  "response_text": "Given your time constraint, I've come up with a 5-minute healthy breakfast plan for a week. These ideas are quick, easy, and can be prepared in no more than 5 minutes:\n\nMonday: **Yogurt Parfait**\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt\n- 1/2 cup mixed berries (fresh or frozen)\n- 1 tablespoon granola\nCombine all ingredients in a container and grab it on your way out. (Prep time: 2 minutes)\n\nTuesday: **Peanut Butter Banana Toast**\n- 1 slice whole-grain bread\n- 1/2 banana, sliced\n- 1 teaspoon peanut butter\n Toast the bread, spread with peanut butter, and top with banana slices. (Prep time: 2 minutes)\n\nWednesday: **Overnight Oats**\n- Prepare a jar or container with 1/2 cup rolled oats, 1/2 cup milk, and your choice of nuts or fruit the night before. In the morning, grab the jar and go. (Prep time: 1 minute in the morning)\n\nThursday: **Hard-Boiled Eggs and Fruit**\n- Boil eggs the night before and keep them in the fridge.\n- 1 hard-boiled egg\n- 1 piece of fresh fruit (e.g., apple, orange)\n Grab the egg and fruit, and you're out the door. (Prep time: 1 minute)\n\nFriday: **Avocado Toast**\n- 1 slice whole-grain bread\n- 1/2 avocado, mashed\n Toast the bread, mash the avocado, and spread it on the toast. (Prep time: 2 minutes)\n\nSaturday: **Smoothie**\n- Prepare a smoothie the night before or use a pre-made mix.\n- 1 cup smoothie\n Grab the smoothie and go. (Prep time: 1 minute)\n\nSunday: **Muffin and Fresh Fruit**\n- Prepare a batch of healthy muffins on the weekend.\n- 1 muffin\n- 1 piece of fresh fruit\n Grab the muffin and fruit, and you're ready to go. (Prep time: 1 minute)\n\nThese breakfast ideas are quick, nutritious, and can be prepared in no more than 5 minutes. You can also customize them to suit your dietary preferences and ingredient availability.",
